{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Short Answer","anchor":"Short-Answer"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes, the FreemiumKit SDK ships with a built-in parental gate. Just call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FreemiumKit.shared.enableParentalGate(options:)"},{"text":" upon app start.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Full Answer","anchor":"Full-Answer"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We‚Äôve built a simple math-based parental gate that will ask a random multiplication question with numbers from 2 to 10. This should be easy enough for any parent to solve, but tricky enough to avoid small children (6 or younger) accidentally getting into the paywall, as required by the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/app-store\/review\/guidelines\/#kids-category","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for apps in the Kids category.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Just tell our SDK that it should use a parental gate before showing the paywall upon app start, like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import FreemiumKit","","@main","struct AwesomeApp: App {","   init() {","      FreemiumKit.shared.enableParentalGate(options: ParentalGateOptions())","   }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This single line will already work! üéâ But it will use the default system colors (black\/white\/accent) which can look off.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You probably want to customize the parental gate to look nicer to fit your apps playful color scheme, like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import FreemiumKit","","@main","struct AwesomeApp: App {","  init() {","    FreemiumKit.shared.enableParentalGate(","      options: ParentalGateOptions(","         background: .linearGradient(","       